        "content": "<p>With the current tactic</p>\n<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"548696\">Michał Mrugała</span> <a href=\"#narrow/channel/113488-general/topic/Projection.20of.20twisted.20cubic.20using.20Gr.C3.B6bner.20bases.2BMacaulay2/near/509521144\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>This is a side point: do you think that with your API you could determine minimal generating sets defining Veronese and Segre surfaces? Could you prove that the generating sets usually cited in the literature are generating?</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>With the current tactic, I don't think its possible yet (tactic only is able to do ideal membership over \"nice\" polynomial rings), but I think as I extend the functionality to be able to handle more of M2's, it should be more than possible. I don't have that deep of alggeo experience yet to fully know yet though, so take that with a grain of salt.</p>",
